Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Fisherman's Bible
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:  220
Edition:
Quote:  SEVEN-GILLED SHARK <i>Notorynchus cepedianus:</i> Not regarded as harmful to man in New Zealand, but any shark of ten feet (3.04m) could well be. Its Maori name, `Tuatini', comes from the strangely shaped teeth, with which weapons were made.
